(1,1)
\left(1+\Delta x, \frac{1}{(1+\Delta x)^2}\right)
\Delta x \ne 0
\frac{\Delta y}{\Delta x} =\frac{\frac{1}{(1+\Delta x)^2}-1}{(1+\Delta x)-1} = \frac{\frac{1}{(1+\Delta x)^2}-1}{\Delta x} = \frac{1-(1+\Delta x)^2}{(1+\Delta x)^2\Delta x} = \frac{1-1-2\Delta x -(\Delta x)^2}{(1+\Delta x)^2\Delta x} = \frac{-2 -\Delta x}{(1+\Delta x)^2}
\lim_{\Delta x\rightarrow0} \frac{\Delta y}{\Delta x} = \lim_{\Delta x\rightarrow0} \frac{\frac{1}{(1+\Delta x)^2}-1}{(1+\Delta x)-1} = \lim_{\Delta x\rightarrow0} \frac{\frac{1}{(1+\Delta x)^2}-1}{\Delta x}
\Delta x=0
\frac{0}{0}
\Delta x
\Delta x = 0
f'(1)=\lim_{x \to 1}\frac{f(x)-f(1)}{x-1}=\lim_{x \to 1}{\frac{\frac{1}{x^2}-1}{x-1}}= \lim_{x \to 1}{\frac{\frac{1-x^2}{x^2}}{x-1}} =\lim_{x \to 1}{\frac{(1-x)(1+x)}{x^2(x-1)}} =\lim_{x \to 1}{\frac{-(1+x)}{x^2}}=-2
